---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="python">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    Python Loops
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      Loops allow you to execute a block of code repeatedly. Python provides two types of loops: <code>for</code> loops for iterating over sequences, and <code>while</code> loops for repeating while a condition is true.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">For Loops</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`# Basic for loop with range
for i in range(5):
    print(i)  # 0, 1, 2, 3, 4

# range with start, stop, step
for i in range(2, 10, 2):
    print(i)  # 2, 4, 6, 8

# Looping through a list
fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
for fruit in fruits:
    print(fruit)

# Looping with index using enumerate
for index, fruit in enumerate(fruits):
    print(f"{index}: {fruit}")

# Looping through a string
for char in "Python":
    print(char)

# Looping through a dictionary
person = {"name": "John", "age": 30, "city": "New York"}
for key in person:
    print(f"{key}: {person[key]}")

# Looping through key-value pairs
for key, value in person.items():
    print(f"{key}: {value}")

# Nested for loops
for i in range(3):
    for j in range(2):
        print(f"i={i}, j={j}")`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">While Loops</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`# Basic while loop
count = 0
while count < 5:
    print(count)
    count += 1

# While loop with user input
password = ""
while password != "secret":
    password = input("Enter the password: ")
print("Access granted!")

# Infinite loop with break
while True:
    user_input = input("Enter 'quit' to exit: ")
    if user_input == "quit":
        break
    print(f"You entered: {user_input}")

# Continue statement
for i in range(10):
    if i % 2 == 0:  # Skip even numbers
        continue
    print(i)  # 1, 3, 5, 7, 9

# Else clause with loops
for i in range(5):
    print(i)
else:
    print("Loop completed successfully")

# This won't print the else clause because of break
for i in range(5):
    if i == 3:
        break
    print(i)
else:
    print("This won't print")`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Loop Control Statements</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">break</strong>: Exit the loop immediately</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">continue</strong>: Skip to next iteration</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">pass</strong>: Do nothing (placeholder)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">else</strong>: Execute after normal loop completion</li>
        <li>Use <code class="bg-custom-primary text-custom-secondary px-1 rounded text-sm">range()</code> for numerical loops</li>
        <li>Use <code class="bg-custom-primary text-custom-secondary px-1 rounded text-sm">enumerate()</code> when you need indices</li>
        <li>Avoid infinite loops with proper exit conditions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>